==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unisonant
<hw>U*nis"o*nant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets>
+ <ets>sonant</ets>. See <er>Unison</er>.]</ety> <def>Being in unison;
having the same degree of gravity or acuteness; sounded alike in
pitch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unisonous</ent>⟦br⟧
